These notes serve to show that the Egerton MS. belonged to Sir William0Alford at the beginning of the seventeenth century3 and that it was examined, if not owned, by Richard Gascoigne in 1624 and Henry Paget in 1650. The name Steven I cannot connect with any probable owner of the volume, and it may be disregarded. The Alfords had occupied the site of Meaux abbey from the middle of the sixteenth century under the duke of N orthumberland and the earl of Leicester.
